  "content": "To use async/await in Node.js, you need to define an async function. Here's an example:

async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const result = await someAsyncOperation();
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
  }
}

Make sure to always wrap your await calls in try-catch blocks for error handling."
